@Reasoning:
Round-trip stress test for CSS function calls inside property values:
rgb(...) and calc(...). The parser must handle nested parens and
commas inside function arguments without confusing them with the
declaration separator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Same three-stage pipeline as the simple round-trip but with
"div { background: rgb(255, 0, 0); width: calc(100% - 20px); }"
as input. Each null path emits a distinct [FAIL] reason.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input with rgb() and calc() -> [PASS]
- Parser confuses "," inside rgb() with declaration separator ->
  [FAIL] parsing (functions)
- Emitter drops one of the function calls -> [FAIL] HIR->CSS (functions)
@End TestCases

